<p>Choosing the right words can feel overwhelming, but focusing on genuine empathy and offering support are key.  Avoid generic phrases and instead personalize your message to reflect your unique relationship with the deceased and your understanding of their impact on others.  Remember to maintain a respectful and comforting tone throughout your message, focusing on positive memories and offering a sense of peace.  Consider the recipient's emotional state and tailor your message accordingly, keeping it concise and heartfelt.</p>
    

